############################
#################
# adjust shipping offer variable
##########################
##
bad_N =['6','8','1''3','2','5','.','-']
df['special_shipping_offer']=df['special_shipping_offer'].astype(str).str[0].replace('$','').replace('9','').replace('`',''). replace(
    bad_N ,'').replace('3','').replace('1','').replace('','NAN').replace('7','')
                                                                    
df['special_shipping_offer']

df['special_shipping_offer']= df['special_shipping_offer'].replace('P','pick up').replace('U','Unknow').replace(
    'f','free shipping').replace('s','download').replace('p','pick up').replace('d','digit access').replace(
 'o','digit access').replace('S','pick up').replace('v','variable shipping').replace('C','pick up').replace(
    'A','pick up').replace('m','free shipping').replace('e','pick up').replace('i','pick up').replace(
    'w','free shipping').replace('O','pick up').replace('c','free shipping').replace('a','pick up').replace(
    'N','pick up').replace('F','free shipping').replace('l','digit access')

# remove bad character function
def remove(list): 
    list = [''.join(x for x in i if x.isalpha()) for i in list]
                    
    return list

# extract the first few letters as signal represent of
# why_buy variable
sig=[]
for z in ss:
    sig.append(z[0])
print(sig)

# getting dummies variables for different category variables
dummies = pd.get_dummies(df[['season_display','offer_type','offer_program','promoted','holiday_display','level1_category_name',
                            'special_shipping_offer','why_buy']],
                        columns =['season_display','offer_type','offer_program','promoted','holiday_display','level1_category_name',
                                'special_shipping_offer','why_buy'],
                        prefix = ['Season_Display','Offer_Type','Offer_Program','Promoted','Holiday_Display','level1_category_name','special_shipping_offer'
                                 ,'why_buy'], drop_first=True)

columns =['season_display','offer_type','offer_program','promoted','holiday_display','level1_category_name',
         'special_shipping_offer','why_buy']
df = pd.concat([df,dummies], axis=1)
df.drop(columns, axis=1, inplace=True)

#############################
# process missing valve     #
# for continue data         #

Imputer = SimpleImputer(missing_values = np.NaN, strategy ='most_frequent')
Imputer.fit((df[['discount','RPC ','comission_rate','conversion_rate','revenue','rank','sale_amount']].values))
df[['discount','RPC ','comission_rate','conversion_rate','revenue','rank','sale_amount']]=Imputer.transform(df[['discount','RPC ','comission_rate','conversion_rate','revenue','rank','sale_amount']].values)
